  <para xml:id="p1">
    <p>This is a test of typesetting ancient Greek with LaTeX:</p>
  </para>
  <para xml:id="p2">
    <p><text xml:lang="el">’Εν ἀρχ ῃ ’ ην ‛ο λ´ογος…</text></p>
  </para>
  <para xml:id="p3">
    <p>Here’s the correspondance between ”greek” and ”latin” encoding for TeX:<break/><text font="typewriter">a b g d e z h j i k l m n x o p r s t u f q y w c</text> <break/><text xml:lang="el">α β γ δ ε ζ η ϑ ι ϰ λ μ ν ξ ο π ρ ς τ υ φ χ ψ ω ς</text></p>
  </para>
  <para xml:id="p4">
    <p>A simple example how to get accents and spirits: <break/><text font="typewriter">’a ‘a  a &gt;a &lt;a a| &gt; a| "i "’i</text> <break/><text xml:lang="el">ά ὰ  α ἀ ἁ ᾳ ’ ᾳ ϊ ΐ</text></p>
  </para>
